<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-tablet-text-align-justify has-mobile-text-align-justify"><strong>How is CGPA calculated in VTU</strong> <strong>202</strong>4</h2>



<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;" class="ek-underline">Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA)</span></strong>: </p>



<p class="has-tablet-text-align-justify has-mobile-text-align-justify">A student&#8217;s total academic achievement throughout all semesters is measured cumulatively by the CGPA. It is computed by allocating grade points to the marks attained in distinct courses, offering a comprehensive picture of the student&#8217;s reliability and competence. This all-inclusive score provides a representation of academic competence across the course of the program, encapsulating the B.E. experience.</p>



<p><strong>CGPA = ∑(Ci x Si) / ∑ Ci</strong></p>



<p class="has-tablet-text-align-justify"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;" class="ek-underline">Semester Grade Point Average (SGPA)</span></strong>: </p>



<p class="has-tablet-text-align-justify has-mobile-text-align-justify">In contrast, SGPA is a period-specific assessment that provides information about a student&#8217;s performance within a particular academic term. Similar to CGPA, SGPA is a measure of a student&#8217;s academic performance for a particular semester. Students may evaluate their performance in real time and pinpoint areas for growth with the help of this useful tool. For SGPA Calculator <a href="/vtu-sgpa-calculator/" class="ek-link">click here</a></p>



<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;" class="ek-underline">Academic Rigor and assessment</span></strong>: </p>



<p class="has-tablet-text-align-justify has-mobile-text-align-justify">The thorough assessment system that molds students&#8217; academic paths is the embodiment of VTU&#8217;s academic rigor. As indicators of academic performance, the CGPA and SGPA systems offer a thorough picture of a student&#8217;s accomplishments during their B.E. degree.</p>



<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;" class="ek-underline">Continuous Assessment and Growth</span></strong>: </p>



<p>VTU&#8217;s dedication to ongoing evaluation and development is emphasized via the CGPA and SGPA systems. These measures take into account success on a variety of evaluations, projects, and practical exams rather than just end-of-term exams. Students are encouraged to continually apply themselves through this comprehensive evaluation technique, which promotes a culture of continuous progress.</p>



<div style="height:26px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Exploring the VTU Grading System</strong></h3>



<p class="has-tablet-text-align-justify has-mobile-text-align-justify">Let&#8217;s delve into the distinctive aspects of this calculator after gaining a comprehensive understanding of the VTU grading system. VTU employs a 10-point grading system, wherein every subject undergoes evaluation based on a letter grade and its corresponding grade points.</p>



<p><strong>Grade Points</strong>: VTU employs a scale from 0 to 10, with A (Excellent) equating to 10 and F (Fail) assigned a value of 0.</p>



<p>SGPA reflects the average of the grade points obtained in all subjects during that specific semester.</p>



<p>The CGPA is calculated by summing the SGPA for each semester.</p>



<div style="height:17px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



